								<h2 class="font-weight-semibold mb-md">DTP-containing vaccine</h2>
								<p class="lead font-weight-normal">The DTaP vaccine protects your child against three diseases: diphtheria, tetanus, and pertussis (whooping cough).

										</p>

								<img src="images/dptvaccine.jpg" style="max-width: 260px;" alt="" class="pull-right ml-xl mb-xl img-responsive box-shadow-custom" />

								<p>The DTaP vaccine protects your child against three diseases: diphtheria, tetanus, and pertussis (whooping cough).<br>
Diphtheria : <br>
This bacterial infection causes fever, weakness, and a sore throat. A thick, gray coating develops in the back of the throat, which makes it hard to breathe or swallow and sometimes results in suffocation.
<br>Tetanus : <br> (also called lockjaw) is a bacterial infection.The bacteria live in soil and dust and enter the body through a break in the skin. People get tetanus from puncture wounds, burns, and other injuries – sometimes even minor ones.
<br>Pertussis : <br> better known as whooping cough, is a very contagious bacterial infection and one of the most common vaccine-preventable childhood diseases.
								<div class="toggle toggle-primary toggle-simple" data-plugin-toggle>
