										<div class="toggle-content">
											<p>Are there any reasons why my baby shouldn’t have the DTP vaccination?<br>
											The DTP-containing vaccine should not be given if
												<ol class="list list-ordened list-ordened-style-2 mb-xlg mt-lg">
												<li>baby has any severe, life-threatening allergies.</li>
												<li>Some children may have a bad reaction to the pertussis vaccine in DTaP and should not take another dose.</li>
												<li>Had a seizure or collapsed after a dose of DTaP</li>
											</ol>
											</p>
											The DTP-containing vaccine can be delayed if your baby:<br>
											<ol class="list list-ordened list-ordened-style-2 mb-xlg mt-lg">
												<li>is not feeling well.</li>
												<li>a mild illness, such as a cold</li>
												<li>has fever</li>




											</ol>
